    <h1>Search filters in the webshop</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Some online shop visitors know exactly what they’re looking for.
For example, imagine you sell shoes.
A customer searches for black Nike shoes that cost less than €150.
Online shop visitors can use search filters to limit which products they see.
The more products a shop category includes, the more important search filters are.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Filters or facets?</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In plentymarkets, search filters are also called <em>facets</em>.
Don’t get confused if someone talks about the so-called <em>faceted search</em>.
This refers to the search filters in the online shop.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<h3 id="_procedure" class="discrete">Procedure</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This function is configured in several different steps:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p><a href="/en/item/frontend-item-search#10">Create the necessary filters</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="/en/item/frontend-item-search#120">Specify which webshop the filters should appear in</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="/en/item/frontend-item-search#150">Design the appearance in the webshop</a>.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="10">1. Creating and editing filters</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>First, create all of the necessary filters.
For example, if customers should be able to search for black Nike shoes that cost less than €150, then you’ll need to create the filters “Colour”, “Brand” and “Price range”.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can <a href="/en/item/frontend-item-search#20">manually</a> create and edit filters or you can <a href="/en/item/frontend-item-search#80">import</a> filters with the help of a CSV file.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="20">1.1. Manual procedure</h3>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="30">1.1.1. Creating new filters</h4>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Client » Settings » Services » Faceted search</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-plus  "></i></span> <strong>New</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings. Note <a href="#table-new-facet">Table 1</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.<br>
→ The filter is created and opened for editing.
Depending on which type of filter you chose, you’ll see some or all of the tabs explained further below.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<table id="table-new-facet" class="tableblock frame-all grid-all stretch">
